only the TOTEM\ndata at the LHC region, the fits with L$\\gamma$ indicate $\\gamma\\sim 2.0\\pm\n0.2$ (AU) and $\\gamma\\sim 2.3\\pm 0.1$ (DDR); (3) by including the ATLAS data\nthe fits provide $\\gamma\\sim 1.9\\pm 0.1$ (AU) and $\\gamma\\sim 2.2\\pm 0.2$\n(DDR); (4) in the formal and practical contexts, the DDR approach is more\nadequate for the energy interval investigated than the AU approach. A review on\nthe analytic results for $\\sigma_{tot}$ and $\\rho$ from the Regge-Gribov, DDR\nand AU approaches is presented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 May 2017 16:42:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 May 2017 17:25:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 11 Nov 2017 21:41:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-15"}
